Cherry blossoms bloom between late March and April, in Tokyo, Osaka and Kyoto.
Japanese people love cherry blossoms not only because they are beautiful but also because they only bloom for a very short period.

âThe kimonoâ is the traditional Japanese national costume worn 
with a sash, or obi. It is principally made of wool, cotton and silk.

Nowadays young people wear the kimono less frequently and only 
for special occasions, such as the New Year's Day, Coming-of-Age 
Day or wedding receptions.

Even though it's beautiful to look at, the kimono does not allow 
much freedom of movement and is quite expensive compared 
to Western clothes.

Few young people can put on a kimono by themselves either, and 
some go to kimono schools to learn how to put one on.

The informal cotton kimono worn in the summer is called yukata.

primary_host.about:
Hello there, I am Masami!
I live with my husband.
I was born and raised in Shibuya Hatagaya.

The cat in the picture named Mewmew and he is 21 years old now.
I conserved him at a shrine when he was a kitten like 13cm small.

I used to be a stage actress and am now a web designer and works at Omote Sandou.
I go to work by bike when it is sunny outside.

Here Hatagaya area is pretty close to Shinjuku and Shibuya which are the center of downtown Tokyo.
It is really handy to reach the downtown but you still can feel the local enough.
Welcome to Tokyo, have tons of fun!

A comfortable space that can accommodate up to 2 people.
This apartment is 3mins from Shinjuku by train and also close to Shibuya !
It is a 6-minute walk from the nearest station of the apartment.
The apartment is in a residential area so you can sleep peacefully and sleep at night.
It is tourist friendly town includes a shopping street.

sorted_reviews.comments: Such a beautiful, clean and homely space. Masami communicated every detail clearly and kindly. Can't wait to come back and stay here again!
sorted_reviews.response: Thanks for your review!See you next time !

sorted_reviews.comments: The location of this place is amazing!!! the place itself if nice, but the truly spectacular part is how close you are to EVERYTHING!!!
sorted_reviews.response: Thanks for your review!See you next time !

sorted_reviews.comments:
We really enjoyed staying at Masamiâs place! Although the space is small, we never had an issue with 2 people and Masami has made every effort to provide everything you need. She is also quick to respond to all enquiries. The apartment is well-located a 5 min walk away from the local subway station, which is only 2 stops away from Shinjuku.
Overall, we would highly recommend this apartment for anyone looking to stay in Tokyo!
sorted_reviews.response: Thanks for your review!See you next time !

sorted_reviews.comments:
Whilst the apartment was clean and in a good location, it unfortunately did not live up to the description or photos on the listing. We needed to use both beds and instead of finding two comfortable beds as shown in the photos, the second bed was a very thin futon which was extremely uncomfortable. We found it so uncomfortable that we had to leave early and find other accommodation in the area.

The apartment was very small and when we put the second bed out there was no room at all for our luggage. For a single traveler this apartment would be okay.
sorted_reviews.response: Thanks for your review!See you next time !

sorted_reviews.comments: EXCELLENT PLACE!! Masamiâs place at Calm Hatagaya is incredibly well placed yet far enough to make you feel like a local and tourist at the same time! She was spot on with all amenities provided and extremely thoughtful instructions for people like myself where my japanese isnât as good as I would like! Overall a great experience and I would highly recommend using Masami! Will definitely be returning soon!
sorted_reviews.response: Thanks for your review!See you next time !

sorted_reviews.comments: Great location, Great place, Great host, couldn't have asked for more
sorted_reviews.response: Thanks for your review!See you next time !

sorted_reviews.comments: Masamiâs place was easy to get to and find, the instructions to enter the property (and overall) were very clear and concise, and the room was great! It easily fit 2 people and Masamiâs hospitality was fantastic! The area was very quiet but close to the train station where it was a short trip to Shinjuku. It was so great having her as a host :)
sorted_reviews.response: Thanks for your review!See you next time !
